It can be shown: if formula_90, then formula_103 for some place &quot;q&quot; of the residue field formula_104 of &quot;p&quot;. (Observe formula_105 is a valuation ring of formula_104 and let &quot;q&quot; be the corresponding place; the rest is mechanical.) If &quot;D&quot; is a valuation ring of &quot;p&quot;, then its Krull dimension is the cardinarity of the specializations other than &quot;p&quot; to &quot;p&quot;. Thus, for any place &quot;p&quot; with valuation ring &quot;D&quot; of a field &quot;K&quot; over a field &quot;k&quot;, we have:

:formula_107.

If &quot;p&quot; is a place and &quot;A&quot; is a subring of the valuation ring of &quot;p&quot;, then formula_108 is called the &quot;center&quot; of &quot;p&quot; in &quot;A&quot;.

=== Places at infinity ===
For the function field on an affine variety formula_7 there are valuations which are not associated to any of the primes of formula_7. These valuations are called the places at infinity. For example, the affine line formula_111 has function field formula_112. The place associated to the localization of
:formula_113
at the maximal ideal
:formula_114
is a place at infinity.

